## Build Sequence Dependency Graph

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    classDef foundation fill:#1a1a2e,stroke:#e94560,color:#fff
    classDef data fill:#16213e,stroke:#0f3460,color:#fff
    classDef auth fill:#0f3460,stroke:#533483,color:#fff
    classDef ui fill:#533483,stroke:#e94560,color:#fff
    classDef core fill:#e94560,stroke:#fff,color:#fff
    classDef final fill:#388E3C,stroke:#1B5E20,color:#fff

    P1[Phase 1: Scaffolding]:::foundation --> P2[Phase 2: Database]:::data
    P2 --> P3[Phase 3: Auth]:::auth
    P1 --> P4[Phase 4: Gallery UI]:::ui
    P2 --> P4
    P3 --> P5[Phase 5: Booking]:::core
    P4 --> P5
    P5 --> P6[Phase 6: Payment]:::core
    P6 --> P7[Phase 7: Dashboards]:::core
    P7 --> P8[Phase 8: Polish]:::final
```

---

## Time Estimate Summary

| Phase | Hours | Parallel? |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1. Scaffolding | ~2h | No — must be first |
| 2. Database | ~2h | No — needs Phase 1 |
| 3. Auth + Profiles | ~3h | Can overlap with Phase 4A |
| 4A. Landing Page + 3D | ~3h | **Yes** — Product Lead does this while Dev does Auth |
| 4B. Gallery UI | ~4h | After Auth |
| 5. Booking + Maps | ~3h | No — needs Auth + Gallery |
| 6. Payment | ~4h | No — needs Booking |
| 7. Dashboards | ~3h | No — needs Payment |
| 8. Polish | ~3h | **Yes** — All hands |
| **TOTAL** | **~27h** | With parallelization: **~22-24h** |

> [!WARNING]
> 4-day hackathon = ~48 working hours max.
> We use ~24h on code, leaving ~24h for design, pitch deck, sleep, and debugging.
> This is tight but achievable if we follow the sequence.

